Schema illustrating the flow of the request when typing "https://www.google.com" in the browser:

Diagram link: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Bpg33srtHGtKbhqD4VE9qfmV7WYV-Aha/view?usp=drive_link


In this diagram:

The request begins with DNS resolution, translating the domain name "www.google.com" to an IP address.
The request is encrypted (HTTPS) and passes through a firewall for security.
The encrypted request hits the server IP on the appropriate port.
The request is distributed via a load balancer to ensure efficient resource utilization.
The web server serves a web page in response to the request.
The application server generates the web page, possibly querying a database for data.
